</address></addressbook></inventor><inventor sequence="02" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>XIAO</last-name><first-name>YUN</first-name><address><city>Shenzhen</city><country>CN</country></address></addressbook></inventor><inventor sequence="03" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>PI</last-name><first-name>SHANG-HUI</first-name><address><city>Shenzhen</city><country>CN</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A method for verifying signatures includes the following steps. Generate corresponding input signals in response to user's operation for inputting a signature on an electronic device. Then detect coordinates of the handwriting of the user's signature. Extract the feature of the user's signature according to the detected coordinates. Generate a user identifier according to the extracted feature of the user's signature, and transmit the extracted feature of the user's signature and the generated user identifier to a server. Retrieve the feature of signature corresponding to the user identifier recording in the storage unit. And finally, compare the retrieved feature of signature with the received feature of the user's signature transmitted from the electronic device, to verify whether they are the same; and transmit the verified result to the electronic device. An electronic device and a signature verifying system are also provided.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>